Codex Desktop for Linux
=======================

This package installs the repacked Codex Desktop bundle from this repository
under /opt/codex-desktop and adds a launcher at /usr/bin/codex-desktop.

The desktop app still needs the Codex CLI to exist on the machine as the
`codex` command. Install it with:

  npm i -g @openai/codex

If you install the CLI through nvm, the desktop launcher tries a few common
locations such as ~/.nvm/versions/node/*/bin/codex. If that still does not
work, set CODEX_CLI_PATH explicitly before launching the app.
